cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a method for temporal model adaptation, which involves learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also uses a graph-based approach, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and the problem of person re-identification involves security and surveillance, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
